verbose_text: Premature ovarian insufficiency (POI) is defined as the syndrome of ovarian function depletion before the age of 40 years, with oligo / amenorrhoea and increased follicle stimulating hormone (FSH) concentration (> 25 IU/l), recorded at least twice, four weeks apart [XREF_BIBR].
